pull_request.title: Implemented delete URL endpoint
pull_request.body:
## Description
Implemented the option to delete a URL endpoint for all storage drivers. The DELETE http verb can now be passed with the curl command. Another change was made as well: for the file storage driver, a directory called 'urls' (default path) is created automatically if it does not already exist and no other path is specified.

## Issue ticket link
https://github.com/kamaln7/klein/issues/14

## How has this been tested?
Tested using memory and file storage drivers. Sample run:
![memory](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/59581465/205461896-6b119dc2-de43-497d-876e-69698c83b423.jpg)

issue.title: X Error of failed request:  BadLength (poly request too large or internal Xlib length error)
issue.body:
I tried to open the st terminal and open the configuration polybar via vim and I searched for /poly and suddenly the terminal came out,
and there is a message , but in xfce4-terminal it's fine with vim

X Error of failed request: BadLength (poly request too large or internal Xlib length error)
  Major opcode of failed request: 139 (RENDER)
  Minor opcode of failed request: 20 (RenderAddGlyphs)
  Serial number of failed request: 1943
  Current serial number in output stream: 2071

os : Arch
wm : i3-gaps
![2019-09-29-103932_1366x768_scrot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47493498/65825892-b6277b00-e2a6-11e9-8367-dd2c5a4916f2.png)

my st version :  st-0.8.2

comment.body: using the [font2](https://st.suckless.org/patches/font2/) patch (and a fallback to noto) was the best move for me, for those coming here with similar issues but their on `config.h` stuff

```suggestion
	overwrite := r.FormValue("overwrite") == "true"
```
quick way to turn this into a bool from the get go.

pull_request.title: Implemented overwrite parameter
pull_request.body:
## Decription
Implemented an overwrite parameter so that a shortlink can be updated. The ‘overwrite’ parameter needs to be passed with the curl command. If overwrite=true and the alias already exists, the alias is overwritten and used to redirect to the provided URL. If the alias already exists and the overwrite parameter is not included or is equal to any string other than “true”, the alias will not be overwritten and the server will throw the error “alias already exists”.

## Issue ticket link
https://github.com/kamaln7/klein/issues/30

## How Has This Been Tested?
Sample run:

![samplerun](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/59581465/202761397-d82de3e0-dcd3-4c46-9be6-531fee93bc75.jpg)

comment.diff_hunk:
@@ -8,11 +8,11 @@ import (
 type Provider interface {
 	Get(alias string) (string, error)
 	Exists(alias string) (bool, error)
-	Store(url, alias string) error
+	Store(url, alias string, overwrite string) error
comment.body:
```suggestion
	Store(url, alias string, overwrite bool) error
```
This can/should be a bool. You're getting the value from the server as a string, which means at that layer of the program you'll need to address that. Here tho, you control what the interface requires and how it should take in parameters, so a bool is more appropriate
